{
  "texts": [
    "The methodology for text paraphrasing using the PEGASUS model consists of two main stages: pre-training and fine-tuning.",
    "In the pre-training phase, PEGASUS employs a large corpus of text data to learn a large language representation model [35].",
    "This pre-training is conducted using a masked language modeling objective, where certain tokens in the input sequence are randomlyIndonesian J Elec Eng & Comp Sci ISSN: 2502-4752  Academic assistance chatbot-a comprehensive nlp and deep learning-based approaches (Sara H. Anwar) 1047 masked, and the model is trained to predict those masked tokens.",
    "After pre-training, the PEGASUS model is fine-tuned on a specific text paraphrasing task.",
    "Fine-tuning involves training the model on a labeled dataset where each input sentence is paired with one or more paraphrased sentences."
  ]
}